Introduction¶

This data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue. Looking at the Data, we have information about a movie's cast, genre, directors release date, ratings, budget and revenue. From my investigation of this dataset, I want to determine the:

  • Statistical description on the Tmdb Datasets
  • Top 10 movies with Highest Revenue
  • How does the average voting change on the years
  • How does the number of movies released changed over the years
  • What are the properties that are associated with movies that has high revenue

To Start the analysis of the TMDB Database, Let's import all relevant Packages

# Let create a function to find uniqe values for each columns so we can call this at any point during our code
def uni_values(column_Name):
    uni_val = set()
    for value in df[column_Name]:
        uni_val.add(value)
        
    return uni_val

# change datatypes to required format for EDA
df.id = df.id.astype(str)
df.revenue = df.revenue.astype(float)
df.budget = df.budget.astype(float)
df.release_year = df.release_year.astype(str)
df.release_date = pd.to_datetime(df.release_date)
df['release_month']  = df.release_date.dt.month_name()
df['release_week_day']  = df.release_date.dt.day_name()

Conclusions¶

From my study of given dataset, I can conclude that following : we can deduced that the number of movies released increase over the years High revenue movies tend to have a high budget, runtime of around 150-200 minutes, recently release year, high vote_average but peak at about 8.4 and high popularity

This study also has some limitation as a result of the zeros value for budget and revenue column which is above 50% of there data
